# Add Help Menu and Dialog

The goal is to introduce a new 'Help' menu option in the top title bar of the application, positioned immediately after 'Manage Setlists'. Clicking this menu will open a help dialog displaying comprehensive usage instructions and keyboard shortcuts for navigating and operating KeryxPro.

## User Review Required

Please review the structure and content of the proposed help dialog to ensure all required instructions are included and correctly categorized.

## Open Questions

None. The requirements and shortcuts are clearly detailed in the task description.

## Proposed Changes

### Dashboard Widgets

Modifications to the top title bar and the addition of a new dialog widget.

#### [MODIFY] [custom_title_bar.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/custom_title_bar.dart)
- Add an `import` statement for the new `help_dialog.dart`.
- Insert a new `MenuItemButton` labeled 'Help' inside the `MenuBar`'s main level, right after the 'Manage Setlists' `MenuItemButton`.
- Wire the 'Help' button to open `HelpDialog` via `showDialog`.

#### [NEW] [help_dialog.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/help_dialog.dart)
- Create a new `StatelessWidget` called `HelpDialog` returning an `AlertDialog`.
- Implement a scrollable layout (e.g., using `ListView` or `SingleChildScrollView`) containing well-structured sections:
  - **Main Shortcuts**: 'Q' (Song Search), 'S' (Scripture Search), 'L' (Jump to slides).
  - **Bible Search Shortcuts**: Press Enter twice (immediate display), Enter -> Tab -> Enter (add to slides without immediate display).
  - **SetList Shortcuts**: Click item (scroll to slide), Enter on item (display slide).
  - **Slides Shortcuts**: 'Tab' (jump to next immediate blank screen), 'Space bar' (jump to next immediate slide), 'V1', 'C' (jump to specific slide in songs), 'F' (freeze/unfreeze slides).
  - **Other Operations**: Instructions on how to add/edit/delete Setlists, modify presentation settings, and change Monitor 1/2 settings.
- Ensure the dialog matches the app's dark mode visual theme (similar to existing dialogs).

